==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Out-Herod
<hw>Out-Her"od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To surpass
(Herod) in violence or wickedness; to exceed in any vicious or offensive
particular. Compare <er>outpope the Pope</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧It
<xex>out-Herods</xex> Herod.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Out-Heroding</qex> the preposterous fashions of the
times.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outhire</ent>⟦br⟧
